The paper proposes a new type of neural network architecture and a corresponding learning method. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the learning mechanism and optimization of the architecture, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed architecture is also tested on image data, which suggests that it may be applicable to Computer Vision (cs.CV) problems. The paper also mentions the use of relevant input and output neuron pairs, which is a common approach in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed architecture, which suggests that it may be applicable to Systems and Control (cs.SY) problems.
